{
  "texts": [
    "The potential fixes are generated automatically by large language models (LLMs) using data from the codebase, the pull request, and from CodeQL analysis [217].",
    "In particular, when a vulnerability is discovered in supported languages (i.e., JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, and Java), Autofix will generate a natural language explanation of the suggested fix, along with a preview of the code suggestion that the developer can accept, edit, or dismiss.",
    "Moreover, these code suggestions can include changes across multiple files and the dependencies that should be added to the project [68].",
    "Furthermore, a comprehensive evaluation of these AI-driven security tools is imperative.",
    "This involves soliciting and analyzing user feedback, particularly the scenarios where the tools generate inaccurate predictions."
  ]
}